org.knime.core.data.collection

Interface CellCollection

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<DataCell>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CollectionDataValue, ListDataValue, SetDataValue, SparseListDataValue
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AdapterCell, ListCell, SetCell, SparseListCell

    public interface CellCollection
extends Iterable<DataCell>
    Implemented by DataCell, which contain other cells. This is the case for extensions of AdapterValue and CollectionDataValue. It helps the framework to decide whether the contained cell collection contains BlobDataCell, which need special handling upon adding them to a DataContainer.

    Apart from BlobDataCell getting deprecated status soon (use a FileStoreCell instead), this interface should be implemented by any DataCell that writes other cells in its DataCellSerializer.serialize(DataCell, org.knime.core.data.DataCellDataOutput) method.

    Since:
    2.7
    Author:
    Bernd Wiswedel, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland

    • Method Detail

      • containsBlobWrapperCells

        boolean containsBlobWrapperCells()
        Get whether the collection contains special BlobWrapperDataCell (framework use). This method gives a hint to the framework (specifically to the classes DataContainer and BufferedDataContainer) whether they should handle the cell implementing this interface with care with respect to contained BlobDataCell.

        This method should return true only if

        • The iterator returned by Iterable.iterator() implements BlobSupportDataCellIterator (which allows the framework to access the BlobWrapperDataCell without touching the contained BlobDataCell (which is an expensive operation) and
        • at least one element returned by the iterator is indeed a BlobWrapperDataCell.

        Implementation note: This method is really only a helper for the framework. The same information can be retrieved by accessing the iterator. This can be an expensive and unnecessary operation, however.

        Returns:
        Whether the collection contains blob wrapper cells.
